OGG file with the features including Time-stamped metadata:
Digital rights management: OGG files do not support digital rights management (DRM) restrictions, making them ideal for open distribution and sharing.
Chapter support: OGG files can contain chapter markers for easy navigation within long audio tracks or podcasts.
Embedded cover art: OGG files can include embedded cover art images for displaying album artwork in media players.
Time-stamped metadata: OGG files can include time-stamped metadata entries for associating specific information with specific timestamps in the audio.